# Chinese Future-Time Grammar Compared to Polish

## Key Difference (Overview)

- **Chinese** has **no grammatical future tense**.
  Future meaning is expressed using **modal verbs**, **time words**, or **context**.
- **Polish** has:
  - **Simple future** (for perfective verbs)
  - **Compound future** (*będę + infinitive / past participle*) for imperfective verbs

---

## 1. Planned Future — 要 (yào) / 会 (huì)

### Chinese
我明天要去上班。

### Polish
Jutro pójdę do pracy.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 我 (wǒ) — I  
- 明天 (míngtiān) — tomorrow  
- 要 (yào) — going to / intend to  
- 去 (qù) — go  
- 上班 (shàngbān) — go to work  

### English
I am going to work tomorrow.

### Grammar Note
- **要** expresses intention or plan.
- Polish uses **future tense form** of *iść* → *pójdę*.

---

## 2. Neutral Future / Prediction — 会 (huì)

### Chinese
明天会下雨。

### Polish
Jutro będzie padać deszcz.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 明天 (míngtiān) — tomorrow  
- 会 (huì) — will / likely to  
- 下雨 (xià yǔ) — to rain  

### English
It will rain tomorrow.

### Grammar Note
- **会** often expresses prediction or likelihood.
- Polish uses future of **być** (*będzie*) + infinitive.

---

## 3. Scheduled Future (Context Only)

### Chinese
飞机下午三点起飞。

### Polish
Samolot odlatuje o trzeciej po południu.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 飞机 (fēijī) — airplane  
- 下午 (xiàwǔ) — afternoon  
- 三点 (sān diǎn) — three o’clock  
- 起飞 (qǐfēi) — take off  

### English
The plane takes off at 3 p.m.

### Grammar Note
- No future marker in Chinese — **schedule + time word** is enough.
- Polish also often uses **present tense** for fixed schedules.

---

## 4. Near Future — 快要 (kuài yào)

### Chinese
他快要毕业了。

### Polish
On zaraz ukończy studia.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 他 (tā) — he  
- 快要 (kuài yào) — about to  
- 毕业 (bìyè) — graduate  
- 了 (le) — change-of-state marker  

### English
He is about to graduate.

### Grammar Note
- **快要** signals an imminent action.
- Polish uses **zaraz** or future perfective verb.

---

## 5. Future Ongoing Action — 会在 / 要在

### Chinese
明天这个时候，我会在工作。

### Polish
Jutro o tej porze będę pracować.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 明天 (míngtiān) — tomorrow  
- 这个时候 (zhè ge shíhou) — at this time  
- 我 (wǒ) — I  
- 会 (huì) — will  
- 在 (zài) — be doing  
- 工作 (gōngzuò) — work  

### English
Tomorrow at this time, I will be working.

### Grammar Note
- Chinese combines **future marker + 在**.
- Polish uses **będę + infinitive**.

---

## 6. Future Negative — 不会 / 不要

### Chinese
我明天不会迟到。

### Polish
Jutro nie spóźnię się.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 我 (wǒ) — I  
- 明天 (míngtiān) — tomorrow  
- 不会 (bú huì) — will not  
- 迟到 (chídào) — be late  

### English
I will not be late tomorrow.

### Grammar Note
- **不会** negates future expectation.
- Polish negates the **future verb form**.

---

## 7. Promise / Determination — 一定 (yídìng)

### Chinese
我一定会帮你。

### Polish
Na pewno ci pomogę.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 我 (wǒ) — I  
- 一定 (yídìng) — definitely  
- 会 (huì) — will  
- 帮 (bāng) — help  
- 你 (nǐ) — you  

### English
I will definitely help you.

### Grammar Note
- Chinese strengthens future meaning with **adverbs**.
- Polish expresses certainty lexically (*na pewno*).

---

## Summary Table (Conceptual)

- Chinese future = **modal verbs + time words + context**
- Polish future = **verb tense system**
- Chinese verbs **never conjugate**
- Polish verbs **must change form**

